
query number of slave in the kube cluster

$ kubectl get nodes

$ kubectl get nodes -o wide

query number od pods in the cluster

$ kubectl get pods



create container in docker

$ docker run -d --name n1 nginx

Create a pod in kube

$ kubectl run pod3 --image nginx

to see details about a container in docker

$ docker inspect containername


to see details about a pod in kube

$ kubectl describe object objectname

$ kubectl describe pod pod1 | less

press q to come out of the screen

Pod-defination file:

vim pod-defintion.yml

$ kubectl create -f pod-defintion.yml

OR

$ kubectl create -f https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Sonal0409/18Apr-ClassNotes/main/kubernetes/pod-definition.yml
